    },
    {
      "id": "c695g73bTGSWw3MfoKQzh",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1183.8357208102132,
      "y": 1298.9140561241627,
      "width": 152.25987243652344,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0G",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1624888600,
      "version": 506,
      "versionNonce": 287679424,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776357425382,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "chatParticipant\n- chatId\n- participantId",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "chatParticipant\n- chatId\n- participantId",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "92iLrTRFQhnK3GI0JxB_o",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 461.82577609932014,
      "y": 917.7164457874271,
      "width": 1096.8792724609375,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0H",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 822978152,
      "version": 898,
      "versionNonce": 295219048,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776096233883,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "For chat need 2 things:\n    1. Find all participants in a given chat:\n        - use a compositie primary key on chatParticipant table.\n        - we can use participantId as a sort key.\n\n    2. Find all chats where we have participants:\n        - we can use a global secondary index (GSI)\n        - This is fucntion already exists in Dynamo DB -> allows create an index which enable this rapid lookups !",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "For chat need 2 things:\n    1. Find all participants in a given chat:\n        - use a compositie primary key on chatParticipant table.\n        - we can use participantId as a sort key.\n\n    2. Find all chats where we have participants:\n        - we can use a global secondary index (GSI)\n        - This is fucntion already exists in Dynamo DB -> allows create an index which enable this rapid lookups !",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "MRe8SYS3eGVzfOKDMaN5D",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 236.47678796911418,
      "y": 1357.6481987458271,
      "width": 204.6398468017578,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0K",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1030214936,
      "version": 377,
      "versionNonce": 1412137920,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776357217485,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Client A: Websocket1\nclient B: Websocket2",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Client A: Websocket1\nclient B: Websocket2",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ge2Apptqd4oDF_d7-gWug",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1799.2883013394683,
      "y": 1120.7863156193298,
      "width": 1177.899169921875,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0M",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 178194712,
      "version": 866,
      "versionNonce": 474286144,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776357723793,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "This chat server willmaintain all clients connected to it.\nIf a new message is coming, It looks up the participants. then from the hashMap, it finds the respective WS connection.\nsends the message back to the client.\n\nIt is not durable i.e we not storing any msgs -> we rather just receive - lookup - send back.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "This chat server willmaintain all clients connected to it.\nIf a new message is coming, It looks up the participants. then from the hashMap, it finds the respective WS connection.\nsends the message back to the client.\n\nIt is not durable i.e we not storing any msgs -> we rather just receive - lookup - send back.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "z0XQA6EqPyc88GuzS0JXz",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1794.476841316873,
      "y": 1288.863551860359,
      "width": 1524.419189453125,
      "height": 650,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0O",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 984142104,
      "version": 2229,
      "versionNonce": 2109081664,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776357715709,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "For Attachements:\nways:\n    1. Create a new table in Dynamo DB.\n        - So for messages with attachements -> it first writes to the DB.\n        - while sending back, it loads the data and send it back to client.\n        Cons:\n        - Dynamo DB is not really meant for large blob storage\n        - We are over using our chat server for this high band-width usecase of handling media.\n  \n    2. use Blob Storage (AWS s3)\n        - Write those multiple megabytes binary data to S3. It is made to handle for this purpose only.\n        - it has all needs like availability and high throughput.\n    \nHow to reduce the dependncy from chat service Block ? \n    Sol:  Pre-Signed URLs\n          - When Client needs to make an upload -> It requests our chat service for an upload target/url\n          - the chat service is going to use it's auth to ask S3 for an pre-signed url.\n          - \"pre-signed url\": An url that has embedded authentication with some TTL like the url valid for 1 hr or so.\n          - The client will then make a direct request to that blob storage. -> upload the media -> It will have an url that is addressable in the blob storage.\n          - This url can be send inside the message we are sending.\n\n   Thus, Instead of sending a message with the actual media data, we are sending an url of the same referenceing the blob storage.\n\n    Cons:\n        - Need to manage the storage -> shouldn't be used as google drive.\n        - Need to expire the media after some-time.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "For Attachements:\nways:\n    1. Create a new table in Dynamo DB.\n        - So for messages with attachements -> it first writes to the DB.\n        - while sending back, it loads the data and send it back to client.\n        Cons:\n        - Dynamo DB is not really meant for large blob storage\n        - We are over using our chat server for this high band-width usecase of handling media.\n  \n    2. use Blob Storage (AWS s3)\n        - Write those multiple megabytes binary data to S3. It is made to handle for this purpose only.\n        - it has all needs like availability and high throughput.\n    \nHow to reduce the dependncy from chat service Block ? \n    Sol:  Pre-Signed URLs\n          - When Client needs to make an upload -> It requests our chat service for an upload target/url\n          - the chat service is going to use it's auth to ask S3 for an pre-signed url.\n          - \"pre-signed url\": An url that has embedded authentication with some TTL like the url valid for 1 hr or so.\n          - The client will then make a direct request to that blob storage. -> upload the media -> It will have an url that is addressable in the blob storage.\n          - This url can be send inside the message we are sending.\n\n   Thus, Instead of sending a message with the actual media data, we are sending an url of the same referenceing the blob storage.\n\n    Cons:\n        - Need to manage the storage -> shouldn't be used as google drive.\n        - Need to expire the media after some-time.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
